# Frontend Dashboard Core

- Respect `middleware.ts` role guards (`/admin`, `/manager`, `/auditor`, `/settings`). Auditor routes expose only in-progress, submitted, and unstarted audits plus the auditor's own reports — no place or project pages.
- Use `session.userName` and `session.userEmail` for the logged-in user. Do not use `managerAccount.primary_manager.*` for the current user's name or email.
- Reuse shared dashboard components (`FilterPopover`, `AuditDetailView`, dashboard tables, `auditor-display.ts`) instead of one-off list or filter markup.
- Treat `src/lib/api/playspace.ts` and backend responses as the contract source of truth. Place list/filter UIs use `place_audit_status` and `place_survey_status`, not a legacy `status` field.
- Keep `*Row` (preview/list) and `*ExportRecord` (export endpoint) shapes distinct. Use existing row-builder helpers (`auditRowExportRecord`, `projectRowExportRecord`, `placeRowExportRecord`, and full-export `*ExportRecord` helpers) — do not flatten or merge these types ad hoc.
- Every user-visible string belongs in i18n (`messages/en.json` + `messages/de.json`), written from the reader's role and task. No internal model names, backend field names, or implementation jargon in the UI.
- Path alias `@/*` → `./src/*`. Prefer TanStack Query + existing API helpers over new fetch wrappers.
- Manager/admin dashboard page headers use inverted contrast (`bg-foreground` + `text-background`), not a plain `bg-card` shell.
- Admin exports and raw-data views must never expose auditor PII — auditor code only, no names or contact details.
- Contract or role-gated flow changes ship with matching Playwright specs under `tests/e2e/`; coordinate with `qa-e2e-regression` when the backend boundary moves.
- Default git branch is `master` (there is no `main` on GitHub for this repo).
- Never read or edit `.env`, `.env.*`, or secrets unless the user explicitly names that file in the current message.
- Use semantic tokens from `src/lib/design-system.ts` for theming — do not hard-code raw color values. Structural dividers: use `border-edge/<opacity>` (e.g. `border-edge/40`, `border-edge/60`) — not `border-border`. Shadows: `shadow-card` for cards/panels, `shadow-field` for selected-state interactive tiles; avoid generic `shadow-sm/md/lg`.
- `DataTableToolbar` must not carry `border-b`; `CardHeader` in `data-table.tsx` owns that separator — two `border-b` elements in the table header area produce a double-line artifact.
- Admin instrument editor lives in `src/components/dashboard/instruments/`. Instruments have a branch/publish lifecycle — a draft branch is distinct from published version history; do not conflate branch state with version records. Branch state aligns to backend publication rules.
- CDN/asset components live in `src/components/cdn/` (`cld-image.tsx`, `upload.tsx`). Asset types and URL builders: `src/lib/cloudinary-images.ts`; screenshot-path-to-CDN mapping: `src/lib/asset-url.ts`. Asset manifest: `public/asset-index.json` (generated — do not edit manually). Admin asset browser: `src/app/(protected)/admin/assets/`. Requires `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME`. Framed screenshots are no longer stored in `public/screenshots/Framed/` — they are delivered via Cloudinary. Marketing composite images live in `public/marketing/composites/`; see `docs/landing-assets-prompts.md` for generation guidance.
- Bug reporting: in-app components live in `src/components/bug-report/` (dialog, launcher, known-issue match list); admin dashboard components in `src/components/dashboard/bug-reports/` (table, badges, screenshot); feature flags and context in `src/lib/bug-report/`. Bug report API types go in `playspace-types.ts`; client methods in `playspace.ts` under the `admin` namespace. New bug report flows ship with matching Playwright specs under `tests/e2e/`.
